name: everything and nothing (book)
description: "Everything and nothing" is a compilation of digital drawings developed by Romeu Silveira during the quarantine, between the months of March and April 2020. For the creation of this series, various images were digitally transformed into lines, strokes, and then reorganized and recontextualized. The .pdf file has 200 pages, fully illustrated in black and white, and it was published by @editions_zero.
